Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a light-brown pottery jar, the fabric is grey in section, the interior is very worn, the exterior is covered with a light-brown slip and remains of two lines of black-painted hieratic text and traces of a dark-brown resinous deposit suggesting that the contents were incense.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393529) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393529)
